The first set of 100 winners have emerged in the United Bank for Africa (UBA) Bumper account, a hybrid savings account. The winners emerged at the first draw for the year, taking home a cumulative sum of N10 million. The first monthly draw for the Bumper account which is targeted at encouraging a savings culture was held at the UBA head office in Lagos with 100 customers wining N100,000 shopping allowance each. One of the winners, Onyegbulem Peace who was present at the draw, said she had opened the account last year and defied all odds to be present at the draw with the hope of winning. She expressed gratitude to the bank for the money which she won. Another winner, who was also present at the draw, Amos Wisdom appreciated the bank for the draw. Speaking during the launch and monthly draw which was held on Tuesday, the group head, Retail Banking, Jude Anele said, the new ‘UBA Bumper Account’ was created with the customer in mind. Anele said, “We have in recent times deepened our focus on the most important aspect of our business – the customers we serve. Hence, our huge investment in technology to make banking easier and seamless, even as we introduce new offerings such as this Bumper Account, that will deliver improved value to stakeholders. He explained that new and existing customers of the bank need to ensure they have a minimum deposit of N5,000 in their UBA Bumper Account to qualify for draws. According to him, current UBA customers can migrate to the UBA Bumper Account whilst potential customers should open a UBA Bumper Account. He added that a monthly shopping allowance of N100,000 for a year is also up for grabs. “No fewer than 50 account holders will get a whopping N2 million each across all participating regions. This account is open to both existing and new customers of the bank who save a minimum of N5,000,” Anele noted.